// sensor_defs.json is the main translation information from the
//      Slocum glider data variables/sensors to the Profile NetCDF
//      variables. 
//
//  Each entry into the dictionary should have a keyword that is the 
//  glider data variable to use in the NetCDF variable name 
//  "nc_var_name" attribute. The main keyword is not necessarily the raw
//  Slocum data variable name, but may be a secondarily processed
//  variable. The subdictionary for each should have an "attrs"
//  attribute that become the variable level NetCDF attributes. See the 
//  DAC instructions for the required attributes, additional may be added.
//  "dimension" is required and should be `time`, and "type" is required
//  and is the typical NetCDF data types. The attribute "is_dimension"
//  is only required on the time dimension variable (here `llat_time`).
//  The attribute "_FillValue" will dictate what the fill value is for
//  the variable, if excluded, the default fill value from the NetCDF
//  libraries will be used.
//
//  At this time, chlorophyll, oxygen, or PAR can be recalculated from
//  the raw measurement variable in the glider.  Use the instructions
//  found in the upper level "instructions" directory to apply these.
//  Hopefully soon an update will be available for any generic
//  processing to be used on any raw glider data.
//
//  I have left this sensor_defs example/template filled out for usage
//  from OOI Endurance Data, but add any variables needed from your
//  gliders following any of the data variables' examples and remove
//  those not needed. Any added variables will be included in the final
//  Glider DAC product provided they have a valid CF "standard_name"
//  attribute, or the variable name is included in the
//  "ancillary_variables" attribute of another variable with a valid
//  CF standard name.
//
// gliderdac JSON configurations allow comments in the file
// (no inline comments). Any leading whitespace is ignored.
// pay attention to completing JSON syntax though.
